# __APP_NAME__

## Build & Run

```bash
./build.sh              # Debug build (default)
./build.sh debug        # Debug build (same as above)
./build.sh release      # Optimized release build + app bundle
./build.sh dist         # Release build + sign + notarize + DMG
./build.sh clean        # Remove build artifacts

./run.sh                # Debug — runs in terminal, log output visible (default)
./run.sh debug          # Same as above
./run.sh release        # Release — opens .app bundle
```

## Tech Stack

- **Swift 6.0** with strict concurrency
- **SwiftUI** (no AppKit unless necessary)
- **macOS 15+** (Sequoia) — use Observable macro, not ObservableObject
- **Swift Package Manager** — never raw swiftc
- **No Xcode** — everything builds from command line

