## Conventions

### File Naming
- Views: `*View.swift` (e.g. `SettingsView.swift`)
- Services: `*Service.swift` or `*Manager.swift` (e.g. `MIDIService.swift`)
- Models: descriptive name (e.g. `Chord.swift`, `Sequence.swift`)

### When to Create Subdirectories
- `Views/Components/` — when you have 3+ reusable view components
- `Views/Theme/` — when you extract colors/fonts/styles
- New subdirectory in `Services/` or `Models/` — when a domain area has 3+ files

### Commits
- English, imperative mood (e.g. "Add settings view", "Fix MIDI input handling")
- No AI attribution in commit messages

### SwiftUI Patterns
- Use `@Observable` macro (not `ObservableObject`/`@Published`)
- Use `@State`, `@Environment` for view state
- Prefer `@Bindable` for passing observable objects to subviews
- Keep views small — extract components early
